Codex focused pass (2026-06-10): the Binius cone now fails more specifically than the earlier “missing `BinaryBasefold/General.olean`” audit note.

Command tried: `lake build ArkLib.ProofSystem.Binius.BinaryBasefold.General ArkLib.ProofSystem.Binius.FRIBinius.General ArkLib.ProofSystem.Binius.BBFSmallFieldIOPCS`. It reaches `ArkLib/ProofSystem/Binius/BinaryBasefold/ReductionLogic.lean` and fails there. A filtered direct check reports:
- line 40: unknown option `linter.unusedInstances`;
- active stale proof failures around lines 409, 414, 422, 592, 606, 759, 772, 1084, 1278;
- line 1357: unexpected doc-comment token before the residual replacement;
- line 1374: instance synthesis for `FinalSumcheckStepLogicCompleteResidual` fails.

Repo hygiene still reports `scripts/sorry_census.py --fail-on-holes` = 0 holes and `scripts/forbidden_tokens.py` clean, so this is not hidden `sorry` debt; it is a live build/proof-shape failure in the Binius source cone plus the residuals already tracked here.
